In [30]:
# drop column with missing values more than 80%
drop_columns=['PoolQC','MiscFeature','Alley','Fence',]
data_all_c1=data_all.drop(drop_columns,axis=1)

# NA in 'FireplaceQu' means no FirePlace in the house (0.486468)
data_all_c1.fillna(value={"FireplaceQu":"NoFirePlace"}, inplace=True)

# replace 'LotFrontage' NA with median value (0.166495)
data_all_c1.fillna(value={'LotFrontage':np.nanmedian(data_all_c1['LotFrontage'])},inplace=True)

# NA for Garage section means no Garage in the house (0.054471)
values = {"GarageType": 'NoGarage', "GarageYrBlt": 0,"GarageFinish":"NoGarage","GarageQual":"NoGarage","GarageCond":"NoGarage"}
data_all_c1.fillna(value=values,inplace=True)

# NA for Basement section means no basement in the house
values = {"BsmtQual": 'NoBsmt', "BsmtCond": 'NoBsmt',"BsmtFinType1":'NoBsmt',"BsmtFinType2":'NoBsmt',"BsmtExposure":'NoBsmt'}
data_all_c1.fillna(value=values,inplace=True)
